WEBVTT

00:05.422 --> 00:10.582
I went to three Home Depots
to buy toilet seats for Reggie's school.

00:10.719 --> 00:12.795
Jesus Christ.

00:12.929 --> 00:16.879
- Do I have to go to therapy?
- Not if you don't want to.

00:17.017 --> 00:19.934
- Here. Take my picture!
- Why?

00:20.061 --> 00:21.888
Happy thoughts.

00:22.939 --> 00:25.347
For my beautiful young friend.

00:25.483 --> 00:28.687
- I love you, sweetie.
- What are you doing?

00:28.820 --> 00:31.525
Time to shake things up. Piggy-back ride.

00:31.656 --> 00:36.567
- We can't go where they're going!
- Open door's an invitation.

00:36.703 --> 00:38.742
Gotta jump while the door's open!

00:40.000 --> 00:46.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:47.756 --> 00:49.962
And she was gone.

00:50.091 --> 00:53.128
I don't understand. Where did she go?

00:53.261 --> 00:55.930
- She's coming back, right?
- I don't know.

00:56.056 --> 01:01.298
Why do I keep losing all the things
and people that I care about?

01:02.520 --> 01:05.093
That's what life is, peanut.

02:08.752 --> 02:10.829
Since the dawn of man,

02:10.964 --> 02:15.756
we've yearned to emulate a bird's ability
to break free from its earthly bonds,

02:15.885 --> 02:18.555
you know, fly like an eagle. Whatever.

02:18.680 --> 02:21.634
You may soar to metaphorical heights,

02:21.766 --> 02:26.309
but none of us really has wings
and gravity never really lets up.

02:26.438 --> 02:28.679
All things come back to earth.

02:28.815 --> 02:32.564
There seems to be
a gravity for relationships, too.

02:33.820 --> 02:38.281
No matter how high they fly,
they always seem to find their way.

02:38.408 --> 02:41.693
Well, they find their way back home.

02:51.588 --> 02:54.375
- Good afternoon.
- Afternoon.

02:55.633 --> 03:00.212
- Have I done something wrong?
- I can't tell. She's not talking to me.

03:00.347 --> 03:02.553
Are you not talking to him?

03:04.059 --> 03:06.384
Oh, bloody hell.

03:13.151 --> 03:17.398
- Diet Coke, chipped ice, but not too much.
- I think this is about Betty.

03:17.530 --> 03:23.900
I think George has somehow
implicated me in Betty's disappearance.

03:24.037 --> 03:28.699
- Am I right or am I right?
- Can you pass me the ketchup?

03:28.833 --> 03:32.498
- How you doing?
- I don't think so.

03:32.629 --> 03:36.627
That's all you want, the ketchup?
'Cause ketchup I can handle.

03:36.758 --> 03:39.878
But the guilt trip about Betty, that I cannot.

03:40.011 --> 03:42.383
I don't know where Betty is.

03:42.514 --> 03:47.970
- Erm, hello, I'm Mason.
- I don't... think so.

03:49.104 --> 03:51.476
- What does that mean?
- She hates you.

03:51.606 --> 03:55.271
I'm sorry about your friend.
Reapers come and go - that's life.

03:55.402 --> 03:57.893
I missed Betty like crazy.

03:58.029 --> 04:01.481
I had 1,001 questions
and I didn't know where to begin.

04:01.616 --> 04:04.783
Where was she? Was she OK?
Was she coming back?

04:04.911 --> 04:07.319
What did Rube know?

04:07.455 --> 04:13.410
Somebody had to ask him these questions.
Hopefully, that person will be along soon.

04:13.545 --> 04:17.839
- This isn't chipped ice.
- All we've got is cubes.

04:17.966 --> 04:22.129
Well, if you have cubes and an ice pick,
then you have chipped.

04:22.262 --> 04:26.094
- Do you, Casey, have an ice pick?
- Yeah. A nice one.

04:26.224 --> 04:28.929
Well, then, I think we need to start over.

04:29.978 --> 04:33.098
You see that Diet Coke? That's on me.

04:33.231 --> 04:35.687
- I'm Mason.
- You're a fucking moron.

04:35.817 --> 04:39.352
- Is your name Rube?
- It is.

04:39.487 --> 04:43.865
- Well, I'm Daisy. Daisy Adair.
- You're two days early, Daisy Adair.

04:43.992 --> 04:46.234
Well, aren't you lucky?

04:48.955 --> 04:51.576
This is Mason. As we know.

04:51.708 --> 04:55.955
And this is George.
Daisy's one of us. Daisy's a reaper.

04:56.087 --> 04:58.376
George. Is that your given name?

04:58.506 --> 05:02.753
- Georgia.
- That's much prettier. I'll call you Georgia.

05:02.886 --> 05:06.337
I hated her instantly,
with all my guts.

05:06.473 --> 05:09.390
- What is she doing here?
- She was transferred.

05:09.517 --> 05:11.925
- From?
- New York. SoHo.

05:12.062 --> 05:17.056
- Why were you transferred?
- Well, that's kind of personal.

05:17.192 --> 05:21.735
- One Diet Coke, chipped ice.
- Thank you so much, Casey.

05:21.863 --> 05:25.991
So, Daisy...
Now, seriously, that Diet Coke is on me.

05:28.995 --> 05:31.071
Agh!

05:31.206 --> 05:34.539
Excuse me, Miss, I need a refill.

05:34.668 --> 05:37.918
I hated her a little less.

05:43.468 --> 05:45.757
Oh. I'll come back.

05:45.887 --> 05:49.837
- You just came in.
- Forget about it, I'll go downstairs.

05:49.974 --> 05:53.806
Wanna take a bath?
There's plenty of room in here.

05:53.937 --> 05:57.721
Um, I'm grading papers. I just had to pee.

05:57.857 --> 06:00.064
I'll give you your privacy.

06:00.193 --> 06:02.351
You never used to be pee-shy.

06:03.738 --> 06:08.863
You can't talk to me.
Barely make eye contact with me.

06:10.078 --> 06:12.236
Where are you, Clancy?

06:12.372 --> 06:16.322
I'm in the middle of grading papers, Joy.
That's where I am.

06:16.459 --> 06:18.368
Good luck with that.

06:18.503 --> 06:23.498
- I have got 20 papers to read. They all suck.
- Reggie's principal called.

06:27.345 --> 06:30.430
What? Is she stealing more toilet seats?

06:30.557 --> 06:36.180
Just a routine call, he said. Whenever
a student has three absences in a row.

06:36.312 --> 06:39.017
Wanted to know if Reggie was better.

06:39.149 --> 06:42.814
- Reggie hasn't been sick.
- No.

06:42.944 --> 06:48.069
Not fever, runny nose, stuffy head,
can't-get-out-of-bed sick.

06:48.199 --> 06:51.983
- Where the hell's she going?
- To therapy.

06:52.120 --> 06:56.248
Don't you think that
we ought to talk to her, before...?

06:56.374 --> 06:59.577
We? As in you, who's never here,

06:59.711 --> 07:03.791
and me, whose lap
all this crap gets dumped on?

07:06.009 --> 07:09.259
In. You dump something in your lap.

07:09.387 --> 07:11.878
Are you gonna pee or what?

07:18.355 --> 07:21.889
This was the first time
I'd lived alone. I liked it.

07:22.025 --> 07:26.687
At first it was a little too quiet,
but then the quiet became my friend.

07:33.244 --> 07:36.162
Georgia? It's Daisy, Daisy Adair.

07:36.289 --> 07:40.868
- Fuck me.
- I heard that! Open the door, Georgia.

07:44.923 --> 07:48.173
- Evening, roomie.
- What do you mean, "roomie"?

07:48.301 --> 07:51.255
Rube said I should bunk with you

07:51.388 --> 07:54.721
till I find something more... suitable.

07:54.849 --> 07:57.387
Here. It's a housewarming/thank you gift.

07:57.519 --> 08:01.267
- Wood chips?
- No, silly goose, it's potpourri.

08:01.398 --> 08:03.521
It's English Garden.

08:04.567 --> 08:08.897
You're not quite ready for home accents.
Haven't had time to decorate.

08:09.030 --> 08:12.031
It's sort of low on my list of priorities.

08:20.125 --> 08:23.244
You collecting bodies
as well as souls here?

08:24.421 --> 08:28.714
- Oh, Raoul. Poor, stupid thing.
- Raoul?

08:28.842 --> 08:32.791
Homeless gentleman.
Drunk as a sailor but strong upper body.

08:32.929 --> 08:36.760
You know, Daisy,
this is a pretty small apartment.

08:36.890 --> 08:40.260
It really is. Here is the fiver we discussed.

08:40.395 --> 08:43.431
And one cocktail. Ready?

08:46.609 --> 08:48.685
Whoo! Sorry.

08:48.820 --> 08:51.358
I treasure the time we spent together

08:51.489 --> 08:55.569
but you and your smelly self
really must be going.

08:55.702 --> 08:57.244
Whee!

08:57.370 --> 09:02.365
- Mason, be a doll and fetch me that handbag.
- Anything for you, gorgeous.

09:02.500 --> 09:05.952
Was this whole bunking thing
really Rube's idea?

09:06.087 --> 09:08.543
'Cause I don't see him doing that to me.

09:08.673 --> 09:11.793
Georgia, if I may be so inquisitive,
how did you die?

09:11.926 --> 09:15.841
- Why do you ask?
- Well, you seem a little irritated.

09:15.972 --> 09:20.515
I got hit by a toilet seat
that fell from the Soviet space station.

09:20.643 --> 09:24.973
Oh, my God, you're Toilet Seat Girl?
No wonder you're so annoyed!

09:25.106 --> 09:29.685
- Well, I guess we're both famous.
- Well, Daisy, how did you die?

09:29.819 --> 09:33.651
During the making of Gone With The Wind.
I am an actress.

09:33.782 --> 09:35.858
- No way.
- Yes, siree.

09:35.992 --> 09:38.234
Things had been going very well.

09:38.370 --> 09:41.703
The star of the movie and I
had become quite the item.

09:41.831 --> 09:44.287
Hang on. You and Clark Gable?

09:44.417 --> 09:47.204
I was young and didn't know what I was doing.

09:47.337 --> 09:49.744
- Sounds like you did.
- No, I didn't.

09:49.881 --> 09:54.009
I was under the table,
blowing this tall, handsome man

09:54.135 --> 09:58.844
and someone leaned over and whispered
in my ear, "No, that's Clark Gable."

09:58.973 --> 10:01.262
So who were you blowing?

10:01.393 --> 10:05.686
I don't know! It's such a huge cast.
Someone from the confederacy, I think.

10:05.814 --> 10:09.811
But enough about me. Let's talk about
where I'm putting my stuff.

10:11.861 --> 10:14.483
What's happening at school today?

10:14.614 --> 10:17.568
I don't know. Wednesday.

10:17.701 --> 10:22.576
- What is Wednesday? Art or music?
- Gym.

10:22.706 --> 10:27.332
Well, don't you think
you should wear your... tennis shoes?

10:27.460 --> 10:31.209
- They're too tight.
- They fit you just fine.

10:32.382 --> 10:35.715
- So, art was yesterday?
- Mm-hm.

10:35.844 --> 10:37.920
Oh. Did you bring it home?

10:39.889 --> 10:44.053
No. I didn't... It wasn't dry yet.

10:44.185 --> 10:47.804
Oh. OK. I'd really love to see it.

10:47.939 --> 10:51.522
Mr Schiffer wants
to put them up in the classroom.

10:51.651 --> 10:54.522
Reggie, I need to ask you something.

11:01.244 --> 11:03.817
What do you want for breakfast?

11:09.836 --> 11:14.297
- I have to brush my teeth.
- Ocupado!

11:16.760 --> 11:21.885
Do you work for a living?
Because I do and I have to be there on time.

11:23.016 --> 11:25.886
That sounds dreadful.

11:26.019 --> 11:30.764
You know, Daisy, I have a job.
I mean, what do you do?

11:32.609 --> 11:37.022
I'm going to buy the New York Times,
since you don't have it delivered.

11:37.155 --> 11:42.315
Then I'm going to have a green tea and
a muffin and then look for a sweater set.

11:42.452 --> 11:46.948
This afternoon, if I'm so obligated,
I'm going to collect someone's soul.

11:47.082 --> 11:52.621
And if I look really pretty when I'm doing it,
good for me. That's what I do, Georgia.

11:58.468 --> 12:01.422
- You sure you don't want a ride?
- No.

12:01.554 --> 12:04.224
- I have time.
- I like to walk.

12:04.349 --> 12:06.840
OK. Well, have a great day.

